Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously on The Guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.86,0:00:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Talik Allen, six months ago, was an victim of a brutal assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.42,0:00:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Talik put the gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.22,0:00:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Your client has been informed to me twice last time, for molesting an 8-year-girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.30,0:00:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the juvie right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.84,0:00:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm dying... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.54,0:00:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- ALS. Lou Gehrig's disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.46,0:00:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not your associate,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.82,0:00:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a partner and what I'm saying is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.10,0:00:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really, really not so great about being told what to do anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.66,0:00:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you telling me that you are trying to round up enough votes to fire my son?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's uh executive commit meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.32,0:00:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they gonna fire me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.70,0:00:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They are talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.68,0:00:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,资历\N{\fs12}Seniority.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.44,0:00:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,可靠性\N{\fs12}Reliability.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.26,0:01:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,责任感\N{\fs12}Liability.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.49,0:01:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,说重点  杰克\N{\fs12}Get to it, Jake.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.20,0:01:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,资历上  我们在这工作的时间都比尼克长\N{\fs12}Seniority: We've all been here Ionger than Nick.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.00,0:01:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他的名字写在门上  而我们的没有\N{\fs12}His name's on the door ours are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.74,0:01:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,从可靠性来说  尼克有毒瘾  并且在恢复期\N{\fs12}Reliability: Nick's addiction and recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.76,0:01:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我儿子的问题  - 是我们的问题\N{\fs12}- My son's problems-- - Are our problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.58,0:01:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,这就引出了责任感的问题\N{\fs12}Which leads me to liability.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.70,0:01:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,伯顿  尼克搞砸了案子\N{\fs12}Burton, Nick has botched deals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他隐瞒了利益冲突问题  现在又让我们被告上了法庭\N{\fs12}He's hidden conflicts of interest and now he's gotten us sued.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.73,0:01:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,伯顿  我们很尊重你\N{\fs12}As much as we respect you, Burton,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.24,0:01:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们也知道你打算要退休了\N{\fs12}we know that you're planning to retire in the near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.42,0:01:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,而我们需要有一人来接手公司\N{\fs12}and we need someone else's name on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.78,0:01:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,呃  他们  想取消你的合伙人资治\N{\fs12}Well, they, uh, want to revoke your partnership.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他们想让我离开公司吗  - 是的\N{\fs12}- They want me out of the firm? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.32,0:02:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他们选票够吗\N{\fs12}Do they have the votes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.96,0:02:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,斯特拉卡占了九个人中的四票\N{\fs12}Straka has four of the nine locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.40,0:02:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,很接近了\N{\fs12}lt's gonna be close.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.04,0:02:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只有  呃  你和我两票\N{\fs12}We have, well, you and me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.70,0:02:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,那么我们要去说服其他三个人\N{\fs12}and then we're just gonna have to sway the other three.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.60,0:02:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么时候投票  - 星期四  四点\N{\fs12}- When's the vote? - Thursday, 4:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.40,0:02:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我来跟杜赛特谈  她一直想要继续做青石塑料  然后\N{\fs12}l'll talk to Doucette. She always wanted in on Bluestone Plastics and--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.70,0:02:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,好的  我想我能说服比尔·戈登\N{\fs12}Yeah, l think l can sway Bill·Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.10,0:02:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们应该最后找巴里·兰茨堡  他应该是最容易动摇的\N{\fs12}We should save Barry·Landsburg for last. He should be the easiest.
